pr_title: Sampling on the flux space of multiple metabolic networks
pr_body:
Two main modules are included on this PR: 
- about 6,000 bacterial metabolic models have been converted to `.mat` format using the [embl_model_convert.m](https://github.com/hariszaf/dingo/blob/pairs/embl_model_convert.m) script. The The script has been used to convert EMBL models that are publicly available [here](https://github.com/cdanielmachado/embl_gems) as well as models that were built using publicly available genomes and the [`carveme`](https://carveme.readthedocs.io/en/latest/#)  software tool for automatic metabolic modelling reconstruction 
- 2 classes called [`CommunityMetabolicNetwork`](https://github.com/hariszaf/dingo/blob/pairs/dingo/MetabolicNetwork.py#L228) and [`CommunityPolytopeSampler`](https://github.com/hariszaf/dingo/blob/pairs/dingo/PolytopeSampler.py#L302) that enable sampling on the flux space of multiple metabolic networks. 

To enable testing this new module of `dingo` an input example has been added under the [`ext_data`]( https://github.com/hariszaf/dingo/tree/pairs/ext_data/community_models) directory. 

The new module has been integrated in the `__init__.py` and can be used both from terminal and as a function of the `dingo` package.
